First off, thanks a ton for all these packs (new to android and youve made things soo easy!).


...But I'm running into a minor issue. Trying to install the Start Menu v1.1.6, and Ive already have v1.1.2 from one of your other packs. So I figured i could just install it over the top but it gives me an error: 'An existing package by the same name with a conflicting signature is already installed'. Does this mean i have to uninstall the old version first? 

Just wanted to ask before i went and tried that because I assume im going to lose the settings that Ive done to v1.1.2 and if theres a way to avoid that, Id rather avoid it lol.

(also phone isnt rooted and it appears most backup apps need root to save app data)

@diamond-optic

Yep the new version use other parsing packages and this is the reason for the error.Unistall the old version clear data make restart and then install the new version.For backup your settings you need root and one program like titanium backup
